3-D Scalar Glyphs #!N #!EC #!N #!N Scalar glyphs can represent 
3-dimensional as well as 2-dimensional data. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N 
#!N #!I30 #!N 1. Open and execute visual program .../AutoGlyph3DScalar.net. The 
spherical glyphs on the isosurface represent a subset of the data 
elements. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. To visualize the entire data set: 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N a. Disconnect the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Map #!EF output from  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoGlyph #!EF . #!N #!I30 
#!N b. Connect the output of the left-hand  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Import #!EF 
module to the first ("data") input tab of  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoGlyph #!EF 
. #!N #!I30 #!N c. Reexecute the visual program. The number 
of glyphs is greatly increased. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N You can also create your 
own glyphs (both scalar and vector). For example: #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o Connect the output of  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Shade #!EF to the second ("type") input tab of  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoGlyph 
#!EF . #!N #!I30 #!N o Reexecute the visual program. The 
combination of  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Construct #!EF ,  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Connect #!EF , and 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Shade #!EF produces a small pyramidal glyph. #!N #!N See 
AutoGlyph, Connect, Construct, and Shade in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's 
Reference. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next 
Topic #!EF #!N #!N  #!Lt3dvgly,dxall54 h 3-D Vector Glyphs  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
